# 02 — RBAC role assignments (least privilege)

> **Owner: central platform team.** Grants the pilot deploy identity the minimum
> it needs to provision + deploy use-case resources — scoped to the
> **{{RBAC_SCOPE}}** (`{{TARGET_RESOURCE_GROUP}}`), never the subscription and
> never the central hub.

## Principle
- Scope: the target resource group only — `{{RBAC_SCOPE_ID}}`.
- Role: `{{RBAC_ROLE}}` (sufficient for `azd provision` + `azd deploy`).
- For `citadel-spoke` posture the pilot consumes the hub via an Access Contract
  (`citadel-spoke-onboarding`); it receives **no** role on hub resources.

## Commands
```bash
# Resolve the UAMI principal (object) id
PRINCIPAL_ID=$(az identity show \
  --name {{UAMI_NAME}} --resource-group {{UAMI_RESOURCE_GROUP}} \
  --query principalId -o tsv)

# Assign the deploy role, scoped to the target resource group ONLY
az role assignment create \
  --assignee-object-id "$PRINCIPAL_ID" \
  --assignee-principal-type ServicePrincipal \
  --role "{{RBAC_ROLE}}" \
  --scope "{{RBAC_SCOPE_ID}}"
```

> Do **not** widen `--scope` to the subscription or to any central-platform
> resource group. See `../central-platform-boundary.md`.
